text_Basalt: It is dull and flat and usually one color. When there is variation, it tends to look like pock marks
text_Obsidian: It's shiny like broken glass. Also usually one color and dark, but variations in it tend to look painted in

text_Peridotite: preidotite tends to look like green granite (I was onto something when I thought peridot=green!)
text_Pegmatite: Green shows up here too, but there's more variation in color. Rather than being granite-like, it looks more like it's made of crystal shards

text_Gabbro: This is the trickiest pair. It's hard to tell what distinguishes the two. I guess Gabrro is darker and chunkier if that makes sense. A little closer to the solidness of granite
text_Andesite: Andesite is a little lighter. Even when it's dark you can see light-colored variation. It looks almost like it's a pile of ash
